Migrated from [DBZ-7945](https://issues.redhat.com/browse/DBZ-7945)

To rebuild an Oracle materialized view, you would use one of three commands:
{noformat}
DBMS_MVIEW.REFRESH('MV_BASE_TABLE', 'F'); -- Uses Fast Rebuild
DBMS_MVIEW.REFRESH('MV_BASE_TABLE', 'C'); -- Uses Complete Rebuild
DBMS_MVIEW.REFRESH('MV_BASE_TABLE', '? ?'); -- Uses the best choice between Fast/Complete
{noformat}

At least with using the *COMPLETE* rebuild step, both LogMiner and XStream will emit a series of {{DELETE}} events for each row followed by a series of {{INSERT}} events for each row. This can often be problematic as it can cause an unnecessary burst of changes captured by the connector and resent to the Kafka topics.

One interesting point about the materialized view rebuild process is that the rebuild transaction records a unique row into {{MVREF$_RUN_STATS}} table at the outset of the rebuild transaction:
{noformat}
insert into "SYS"."MVREF$_RUN_STATS"("RUN_OWNER_USER#","REFRESH_ID","NUM_MVS_TOTAL","NUM_MVS_CURRENT","MVIEWS","BASE_TABLES","METHOD","ROLLBACK_SEG","PUSH_DEFERRED_RPC","REFRESH_AFTER_ERRORS","PURGE_OPTION","PARALLELISM","HEAP_SIZE","ATOMIC_REFRESH","NESTED","OUT_OF_PLACE","NUMBER_OF_FAILURES","START_TIME","END_TIME","ELAPSED_TIME","LOG_SETUP_TIME","LOG_PURGE_TIME","COMPLETE_STATS_AVAILABLE","TXNFLAG","ON_COMMIT_FLAG") values ('110','1482','1','1','"DEBEZIUM"."MV_BASE_TABLE"',NULL,'F',NULL,'Y','N','1','0','0','Y','N','N','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y','0','0');
{noformat}

What's important to note is the {{METHOD}} field, which will contain either {{F}} for fast or {{C}} for complete rebuilds.  in addition, since this is the first change in the transaction, we could theoretically use this as a flag to discard the transaction to avoid resending the rebuild data to downstream consumers since this transaction is atomic and would only contain changes related to the materialized view rebuild.

For LogMiner, this would mean we need to explicitly add {{MVREF$_RUN_STATS}} to the include list for the LogMiner query we generate.  

This is a bit more intrusive for XStream as the DBA would need to explicitly include this SYS-based table in the list of included tables so that the connector would get this {{INSERT}} operation to flag the transaction for discard.

In either case, we should guard this functionality based on a configuration flag, allowing the user to control whether materialized view rebuilds should or should not be captured.

