# Description:

  When using OpenLogReplicator adapter, the connector fails to resume streaming after restart if OLR send events with SCN lower than the connector's resume position. The root cause is that skipped events are not confirmed to OLR, causing it to reach its internal buffer limit (~60k events) and stop sending new data.

# Reproducer

## Test Case:

  The issue can be reproduced with the following test:
```java
  @Test
  @FixFor("DBZ-XXXX")
  void shouldContinueWithStreamingAfterSnapshotAndRestart() throws Exception {
      Configuration config = TestHelper.defaultConfig()
          .with(OracleConnectorConfig.TABLE_INCLUDE_LIST, "DEBEZIUM\\.CUSTOMER")
          .with(Heartbeat.HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL, "100")
          .build();

      continueStreamingAfterSnapshotAndRestart(config);
  }

  private void continueStreamingAfterSnapshotAndRestart(Configuration config) throws Exception {
      int expectedRecordCount = 0;
      connection.execute("INSERT INTO debezium.customer VALUES (1, 'Billie-Bob', 1234.56, TO_DATE('2018-02-22', 'yyyy-mm-dd'))");
      connection.execute("INSERT INTO debezium.customer VALUES (2, 'Bruce', 2345.67, null)");
      connection.execute("COMMIT");
      expectedRecordCount += 2;

      start(OracleConnector.class, config);
      assertConnectorIsRunning();

      SourceRecords records = consumeRecordsByTopic(expectedRecordCount);
      List<SourceRecord> testTableRecords = records.recordsForTopic("server1.DEBEZIUM.CUSTOMER");
      assertThat(testTableRecords).hasSize(expectedRecordCount);

      // Verify snapshot records
      SourceRecord record1 = testTableRecords.get(0);
      VerifyRecord.isValidRead(record1, "ID", 1);
      SourceRecord record2 = testTableRecords.get(1);
      VerifyRecord.isValidRead(record2, "ID", 2);
      assertThat(record2.sourceOffset().get(SNAPSHOT_COMPLETED_KEY)).isEqualTo(true);

      stopConnector();

      // Insert 100k records into untracked table to create "noise" in redo logs
      Testing.print("Inserting 100k records into dt_table (untracked table)...");
      int batchSize = 1000;
      int totalBatches = 100;
      for (int batch = 0; batch < totalBatches; batch++) {
          int startId = batch * batchSize + 1;
          String plsql =
              "BEGIN " +
              "  FOR i IN " + startId + ".." + (startId + batchSize - 1) + " LOOP " +
              "    INSERT INTO debezium.dt_table (id, c1, c2, c3a, c3b, f1, f2) " +
              "    VALUES (i, i, i, 1.23, 'test', 1.5, 2.5); " +
              "  END LOOP; " +
              "  COMMIT; " +
              "END;";
          connection.execute(plsql);
      }
      Testing.print("Finished inserting 100k records");

      // Insert new record to be captured after restart
      expectedRecordCount = 0;
      connection.execute("INSERT INTO debezium.customer VALUES (3, 'Brian', 2345.67, null)");
