---

## Proposed Fix

Replace the single `long` in `RowIdCodec` with `long[2]` (high 44 bits + low 64 bits) to
store all 108 bits without loss. `LogMinerEvent.rowId` would also need to change from `long`
to `long[]`, along with any downstream callers.

```java
public class RowIdCodec {

    private static final String BASE64_CHARS =
            "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789+/";
    private static final int[] BASE64_VALUES = new int[128];

    static {
        for (int i = 0; i < BASE64_CHARS.length(); i++) {
            BASE64_VALUES[BASE64_CHARS.charAt(i)] = i;
        }
    }

    public static final long[] EMPTY_ROW_ID = encode("AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA");

    private RowIdCodec() {}

    public static long[] encode(String rowId) {
        if (rowId == null || rowId.length() != 18) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Invalid ROWID length: " + rowId);
        }
        long high = 0, low = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < 18; i++) {
            char c = rowId.charAt(i);
            if (c >= 128) throw new IllegalArgumentException("Invalid ROWID character: " + c);
            long overflowBits = low >>> 58;
            low  = (low << 6) | BASE64_VALUES[c];
            high = (high << 6) | overflowBits;
        }
        return new long[]{high, low};
    }

    public static String decode(long[] packed) {
        if (packed == null || packed.length != 2) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Invalid packed array");
        }
        char[] chars = new char[18];
        long high = packed[0], low = packed[1];
        for (int i = 17; i >= 0; i--) {
            chars[i] = BASE64_CHARS.charAt((int) (low & 0x3F));
            low  >>>= 6;
            long borrowBits = high & 0x3F;
            low  |= (borrowBits << 58);
            high >>>= 6;
        }
        return new String(chars);
    }
}
```

**Memory impact per `LogMinerEvent` instance (Compressed OOPs JVM):**

| Storage | Heap per instance | Correct? |
|---|---|---|
| `long` (current) | 8 bytes (inline field) | No — 44 bits silently discarded |
| `long[2]` array (proposed) | 32 bytes (16-byte header + 16-byte payload) | Yes |

At 1 million concurrent events: 8 MB → 32 MB. The overhead is acceptable; silent data
corruption is not.

**Alternative considered:** storing the ROWID as a `String` directly (simpler, no downstream
type changes). `String` costs ≥ 56 bytes per instance on a standard JVM, making `long[2]`
the more memory-efficient correct solution.

